Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
New Base Business Park by AVID Property Group is an 85 hectare master planned industrial estate located in Brendale
on Brisbane’s North Side. The estate is strategically located centrally within Brisbane North, being within close proximity to the Brisbane CBD and outer northern regions including Caboolture and Redcliffe.

The property is located approximately 17 radial kilometres north of the Brisbane CBD in the popular and well established
Brendale Industrial Precinct.

The local area is home to many large organisations including Visy, Aldi, Bunnings, Iplex, Cameron Group, Bureau Veritas, ARB, GE, Weatherford and Super Retail Group (within the estate).
Approximate travel times to major destinations are as follows:

Bruce Highway – 10 minutes
Brisbane CBD – 30 minutes
Brisbane Airport – 20 minutes
Port of Brisbane – 30 minutes

•	Wide frontage to depth ratio
•	Infrastructure credits available
•	Services available for connects
•	Last lots in current stage

Auction on site: 10:00am Thursday, 1st November, 2018

For more information, please contact Exclusive Agents

CBRE is exclusively appointed to offer to the market 20 Belconnen Crescent, Brendale for sale via Expression of interest campaign. This site is one of the last remaining small lots for development in the Brendale region. 20 Belconnen Crescent site poses a fantastic proposition for developers, investors and owner occupiers alike. The site features:

•	2,570sqm regular shaped allotment 
•	Zoned: Industry – General Industry
•	24/7 us allowable under zoning
•	Regular shaped rectangular configuration 
•	Level allotment on natural ground
•	Surrounded by new development 
•	Available for purchase Now

20 Belconnen Crescent is for sale via Expressions of Interest campaign closing 4:00pm Thursday 2nd September, 2020. To make and enquiry to obtain and information memorandum or further information please contact the exclusive agents CBRE.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: ONE OF THE LAST AVAILABLE GENERAL INDUSTRY LOTS

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Central location in high growth area

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Industrial and Logistics is proud to present 31 Johnstone Road, Brendale for sale via EOI campaign. The site is one of the last large scale industrial development sites in North Brisbane. 
The site features:

•	10.38 General Industry Allotment (8.02Ha non easement effected)
•	Flat allotment with level 1 compaction
•	Flexible zoning allowing wide range of uses
•	Services available to site including: Sewer, Water, Stormwater & Data
•	Bulk earthworks completed including batters and bio retention basins
•	Easy connections to major arterial roads
•	Located in Australia’s second fastest growing council

The property is for sale via Expression of Interest closing 18th November 2020 at 4:00pm (AEST)

For more information please contact the Hugh Adnam and Dillon Murphy of CBRE.
